<subSubSection id="8FAA1E8DFFCAFFF9FF6C261EFCAF8DDE" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" type="description">
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFCAFFF9FF6C261EFE938F56" blockId="89.[128,657,918,1763]" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">
IDENTIFICATION: Species identification within the 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFCAFFF9FEF9263BFE4A8D7B" baseAuthorityName="Spix" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[267,449,1065,1088]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bidens">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FEF9263BFE4A8D7B" box="[267,449,1065,1088]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">Tonatia bidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, which includes 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFCAFFF9FF192655FE008D65" authorityName="Koopman &amp; Williams" authorityYear="1951" box="[235,395,1094,1118]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FF192655FF708D65" box="[235,251,1095,1118]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FEFF2655FE008D65" box="[269,395,1095,1118]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, requires reference to craniodental characters described by 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFCAFFF9FDAE2676FED68DA3" author="Williams, S. L. &amp; M. R. Willig &amp; F. A. Reid" journalOrPublisher="J. Mammal." pageId="89" pageNumber="89" pagination="612 - 626" part="76" refId="ref102542" refString="Williams, S. L., M. R. Willig, and F. A. Reid 1995. Review of the Tonatia bidens complex (Mammalia: Chiroptera), with descriptions of two new subspecies. J. Mammal. 76: 612 - 626." title="Review of the Tonatia bidens complex (Mammalia: Chiroptera), with descriptions of two new subspecies" type="journal article" year="1995">Williams et al. (1995)</bibRefCitation>
. Other useful descriptions and comparative measurements of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFCAFFF9FDD1268DFF378DE8" authorityName="Koopman &amp; Williams" authorityYear="1951" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FDD1268DFDB88D8D" box="[547,563,1183,1206]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FDB6268DFF378DE8" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Guianas may be found (incorrectly listed under 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFCAFFF9FE7D26CBFE748DCB" baseAuthorityName="Spix" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[399,511,1241,1264]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bidens">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FE7D26CBFE148DCB" box="[399,415,1241,1264]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FE4126CBFE748DCB" box="[435,511,1241,1264]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">bidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFCAFFF9FDCB26CBFF4C8C36" author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Husson (1962</bibRefCitation>
, 1978), 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFCAFFF9FECA26E4FE4D8C36" author="Hill, J. E." box="[312,454,1270,1293]" journalOrPublisher="Mammalia" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" pagination="553 - 572" part="28" refId="ref95469" refString="Hill, J. E. 1964. Notes on bats from British Guiana, with the description of a new genus and species of Phyllostomidae. Mammalia 28: 553 - 572." title="Notes on bats from British Guiana, with the description of a new genus and species of Phyllostomidae" type="journal article" year="1964">Hill (1964)</bibRefCitation>
, Genoways and Williams (1984), and Brosset and Charles­ Dominique (1990). 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFCAFFF9FE8A2723FD1B8C73" author="Williams, S. L. &amp; M. R. Willig &amp; F. A. Reid" box="[376,656,1329,1352]" journalOrPublisher="J. Mammal." pageId="89" pageNumber="89" pagination="612 - 626" part="76" refId="ref102542" refString="Williams, S. L., M. R. Willig, and F. A. Reid 1995. Review of the Tonatia bidens complex (Mammalia: Chiroptera), with descriptions of two new subspecies. J. Mammal. 76: 612 - 626." title="Review of the Tonatia bidens complex (Mammalia: Chiroptera), with descriptions of two new subspecies" type="journal article" year="1995">Williams et al. (1995)</bibRefCitation>
summarized measurements of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFCAFFF9FE1D275DFD1B8C5D" authorityName="Koopman &amp; Williams" authorityYear="1951" box="[495,656,1358,1382]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FE1D275DFE748C5D" box="[495,511,1359,1382]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FDE0275DFD1B8C5D" box="[530,656,1359,1382]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from throughout its known geographic range. Three subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFCAFFF9FE89279BFD978C9B" authorityName="Koopman &amp; Williams" authorityYear="1951" box="[379,540,1417,1440]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FE89279BFE008C9B" box="[379,395,1417,1440]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FE6C279BFD978C9B" box="[414,540,1417,1440]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are presently recognized: 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FEA327B5FEEA8C85" box="[337,353,1447,1470]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FE8327B5FEF78C85" box="[369,380,1447,1470]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">s</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FE7927B5FE5E8C85" box="[395,469,1447,1470]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">bakeri</emphasis>
(southern Mexico to northern Colombia and northwestern Venezuela), 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FEE327F3FEAA8CC3" box="[273,289,1505,1528]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FEC327F3FEB78CC3" box="[305,316,1505,1528]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">s</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FEB927F3FE118CC3" box="[331,410,1505,1528]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">maresi</emphasis>
(southern and northeastern Venezuela, eastern Colombia, Ecuador, and Peru, the Guianas, and eastern Brazil), and 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FF15242BFF7C8F6B" box="[231,247,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FEF5242BFE998F6B" box="[263,274,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">s</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFCAFFF9FED3242BFE148F6B" authorityName="Koopman &amp; Williams" authorityYear="1951" box="[289,415,1593,1616]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FED3242BFE148F6B" box="[289,415,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Jamaica) (
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFCAFFF9FDD4242BFE808F56" author="Williams, S. L. &amp; M. R. Willig &amp; F. A. Reid" journalOrPublisher="J. Mammal." pageId="89" pageNumber="89" pagination="612 - 626" part="76" refId="ref102542" refString="Williams, S. L., M. R. Willig, and F. A. Reid 1995. Review of the Tonatia bidens complex (Mammalia: Chiroptera), with descriptions of two new subspecies. J. Mammal. 76: 612 - 626." title="Review of the Tonatia bidens complex (Mammalia: Chiroptera), with descriptions of two new subspecies" type="journal article" year="1995">Williams et al., 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFCAFFF9FF6F2466FBA38D4F" blockId="89.[128,657,918,1763]" lastBlockId="89.[704,1233,918,1620]" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">
Our voucher material corresponds closely to Williams et al.’ 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFCAFFF9FE992483FE5E8F93" author="Williams, S. L. &amp; M. R. Willig &amp; F. A. Reid" box="[363,469,1681,1704]" journalOrPublisher="J. Mammal." pageId="89" pageNumber="89" pagination="612 - 626" part="76" refId="ref102542" refString="Williams, S. L., M. R. Willig, and F. A. Reid 1995. Review of the Tonatia bidens complex (Mammalia: Chiroptera), with descriptions of two new subspecies. J. Mammal. 76: 612 - 626." title="Review of the Tonatia bidens complex (Mammalia: Chiroptera), with descriptions of two new subspecies" type="journal article" year="1995">s (1995)</bibRefCitation>
description of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFCAFFF9FF7224BDFE418FFD" authorityName="S.L.Williams, Willig &amp; Reid" authorityYear="1995" box="[128,458,1711,1734]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="saurophila" subSpecies="maresi">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FF7224BDFE418FFD" box="[128,458,1711,1734]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">Tonatia saurophila maresi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with measurement data generally falling within the range of variation they reported; the only exception is the forearm length of one of our females, which slightly exceeds the largest value previously reported for the subspecies. As 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FB6E21FEFB278D38" box="[1180,1196,1004,1027]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FB4C21FEFB428D38" box="[1214,1225,1004,1027]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">s</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FD32261AFC848D24" box="[704,783,1032,1055]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">maresi</emphasis>
is the smaller of the two mainland forms, however, this measurement falls within the known range of variation for the species 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFCAFFF9FD05264FFC1D8D4F" authorityName="Koopman &amp; Williams" authorityYear="1951" box="[759,918,1117,1140]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FD05264FFC8C8D4F" box="[759,775,1117,1140]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FCEA264FFC1D8D4F" box="[792,918,1117,1140]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a whole.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFCAFFF9FD2F266BFCAF8DDE" blockId="89.[704,1233,918,1620]" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">
None of the individuals of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFCAFFF9FBC4266BFC9D8D96" authorityName="Koopman &amp; Williams" authorityYear="1951" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FBC4266BFC9D8D96" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">Tonatia saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that we captured at Paracou folded its ears over the crown of the head when touched.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8FAA1E8DFFCAFFF9FD2F26F8FCFA8F6F" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFCAFFF9FD2F26F8FCFA8F6F" blockId="89.[704,1233,918,1620]" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">
FIELD OBSERVATIONS: We recorded 61 captures (possibly including some recaptures) of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFCAFFF9FD322731FC288C01" authorityName="Koopman &amp; Williams" authorityYear="1951" box="[704,931,1315,1338]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFCAFFF9FD322731FC288C01" box="[704,931,1315,1338]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">Tonatia saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at Paracou, of which 60 were in ground­level mistnets and 1 was in an elevated net. Of the 60 ground­level mistnet captures, 23 were in well­drained primary forest, 26 were in swampy primary forest, 8 were in creekside primary forest, 2 were in closed­canopy secondary growth, and 1 was in a manmade clearing. The only capture we recorded in an elevated net was made at 7–10 m above a treefall in creekside primary forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
